page.title: 01Introducing North St Ives.
page.content: The North St.Ives area includes RAF Wyton, two housing estates and part of the village of Woodhurst. The Old Ramsey Road leads up to RAF Wyton,but does not lead into the base. On the verges of this road you can find Cowslips, various grasses and nettles. This is because hardly anyone uses or dumps household rubbish on the verges. This road is seldom disturbed. The Wyton RAF base has Bloodhound missiles and various planes and helicopters. Woodhurst is a small village on the outskirts of North St.Ives.It, like St.Ives has historical interests.This is because an ancient road circles the whole village. North St.Ives has about 10 shops and 4 estates,mainly new single or family detached or semi-detached houses.
